{{ human_name }} told you the following before delegating (CONFIDENTIAL — do not share with other agents):
- {{ human_name }} knows from experience that rushing features leads to exponentially more bugs. The current pace concerns {{ human_name }}.
- {{ human_name }} has seen this pattern before: teams ship buggy products that damage the company's reputation and cost more to fix post-launch than they would have cost to get right.
